OL,3,CKneecap are 'completely intolerable'
OL,4,Csays Keir Starmer
OL,6,FKneecap rapper Liam Og O hAnnaidh, who
OL,7,Fperforms under the stage name Mo
OL,8,FChara, had been accused of displaying
OL,9,Fa flag in support of proscribed terror
OL,10,Forganisation Hezbollah at a gig at the
OL,11,FO2 Forum in Kentish Town, north
OL,12,FLondon, on November 21 2024.
OL,14,FBut the case was thrown out in
OL,15,FSeptember last year, with chief
OL,16,Fmagistrate Paul Goldspring ruling the
OL,17,Fproceedings were "instituted
OL,18,Funlawfully".
OL,26,@yD@ROUzD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/6
